#ANKI

Control expressions

if
  when none of the conditions in an if statement evaluate as true > if statement returns nil
  
ternary if
boolean? result if true : result if false

Case Statement
  can use to compare against patterns (A?)
  or as if/elsif expression
  can put multiple conditions on the same line
  the first when that matches is executed and all other cases ignored.
  "else" and "then" are optional
  putting when on same line use then
    when 3    then puts "a is three"
  result of case is last value executed in expression
  
  
